<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no" ?>
<FinalDraft DocumentType="Script" Template="No" Version="4">

  <Content>
    <Paragraph Type="New Act">
      <Text>COLD OPEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="1" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. SUBURBAN STREET - DAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A rusting Pontiac chugs down the street. Black and covered with HEAVY METAL ARTWORK (skeletons, demon babes, flaming horses, etc), it sticks out like a sore thumb on this residential block.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="7/8" Page="1" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BRIAN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
              <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Arial" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
            </Paragraph>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="COLBY">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
              <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Arial" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
            </Paragraph>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="GENE">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
              <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Arial" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
            </Paragraph>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HUGO">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
              <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Arial" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
            </Paragraph>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MORGAN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
              <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Arial" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
            </Paragraph>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WINNIE">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
              <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Arial" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
            </Paragraph>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>COLBY AND BRIAN DRIVING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>COLBY REESE (early-30s) rides with best friend BRIAN DORFMAN (early-30s) at the wheel. Quick and energetic, Colby has both the enthusiasm and the self-centeredness of a five-year-old.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They address the camera, documentary style.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>COLBY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>A normal man couldn’t handle this job. People give so much credit to police and firemen. Big whoop. How do you deal with a fire? Spray it with water. How do you deal with a criminal? Handcuffs. But a poltergeist? A space alien? How do you deal with that?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Brian is a hulking, burnt-out goth (black clothes, tattoos, eyeliner). Dark and angsty like a teenager, he speaks with a coarse rasp.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>BRIAN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, firemen are a scam. They probably start more fires than they stop.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>COLBY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Okay, well that’s... not true.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>BRIAN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Prove it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>COLBY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to camera, re: Brian)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This is coming from a guy who huffed so much glue in high school they had to close the art department.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>BRIAN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t remember that happening.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Colby looks to camera: “I rest my case.”</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="End Of Act">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Prime" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Underline">END ACT ONE</Text>
      <Text></Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="New Act">
      <Text>TAG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="6/8" Page="2" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MORGAN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
              <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Arial" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
            </Paragraph>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WINNIE">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
              <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Arial" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
            </Paragraph>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. LASER TAG PARKING LOT - NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>After laser tag. Winnie is in her car.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WINNIE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You sure you don’t need a ride? Or to come over and watch scary movies till the sun comes up? Whichever.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MORGAN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>My car’s just over there.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Winnie looks disappointed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MORGAN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>But thank you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Winnie beams.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WINNIE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>See you tomorrow!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Morgan walks alone through the dark, empty parking lot.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Behind her back, an ENORMOUS WOLF silently lumbers into frame.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>It lets out a surprisingly NASAL HOWL.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Morgan turns. Oddly, this wolf is </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Prime" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Underline">BALD, WITH A TERRIBLE COMBOVER</Text>
      <Text>.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MORGAN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>...Gene?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The wolf SHRUGS and lopes away.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Morgan stares dumbstruck--did she really just see that...?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="End Of Act">
      <Text>END OF PILOT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
  </Content>

